results.occurrenceRemarks: This plant kind of looks like a weed, but I think it may be some sort of tomato plant? I'm not too sure, but it was growing around some other plant that had originally been planted in that spot. The leaves have ridges in them, are broad, and they do have many holes in them.. this is probably from pests. This plant is many 3 feet tall if not smaller, and it has yellow flowers that bloomed from blackish bulbs. They look like upside down bells, and aren't quite fully opened yet.  These flowers do attract a lot of honeybees, as I was able to see from earlier observations.   This plant is native to Mexico (research from this website)

results.occurrenceRemarks: This plant caught my attention because it was growing in dirt by itself, and because of the one flower it had.  The flower was yellow, and it had wavy petals with a sort of black smudge on the inside of the petals towards the stigma. There were several other buds that were in the process of opening as well. The plant itself was about 30 cm tall, and the stem looked about 1 cm in width. The leaves were green and broad; they were smooth and slightly arched. They were round and slightly bumpy as well. I noticed that the younger leaves closer to the buds and the stem of the plant has small ridges on their sides, but I think as they grow more, those ridges smooth out...
